<DATELINE> PROVIDENCE, R.I.  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gtech Corp. said it was tentatively selected by the California State Lottery to provide and service from 2,500 to 7,000 terminals for the state's computerized lottery game.

   Gtech said the contract is subject to a "protest period" and ratification by the California lottery commission, and to a 60-day evaluation of the new terminals' compatibility with the state's existing lottery network.

