<HEAD>One Winner in $37 million Lotto Drawing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One lucky Lotto player received a Christmas Eve
gift that will go on giving for many Christmases to come _ $37
million spread out in 20 annual payments, state lottery officials
said Sunday.
   But the identity of the winner of the third largest grand prize
ever awarded in the Illinois lottery could remain a mystery for a
day or two, said lottery spokeswoman Kathy Rem. State officials have
to certify the winning ticket, and they don't go back to work until
Tuesday, Ms. Rem said.
   The huge payout is the result of three previous weekend drawings
without any player matching all six numbers drawn from among 54
possible. The state lottery guarantees $5 million for each weekend
drawing and rolls that amount over.
   Strong ticket sales added an extra $17 million to the pot to push
the total to $37 million, Ms. Rem said.
   The prize is the fifth largest ever in the United States to go to
a single ticket buyer. The biggest winner is Sheelah Ryan of Winter
Springs, Fla., who won $55.16 million in the Florida lottery in
September.
   Former printer Mike Wittkowski won the largest-ever Illinois
lottery prize of $40 million four years ago.
   Saturday's winning numbers were eight, nine, 27, 33, 43 and 54.
   In addition to the one big winner, 539 players correctly matched
five of six numbers to win $2,365 each, and nearly 32,000 players
matched four to win $80, officials said.
</TEXT>
